reviews.review_text: A beautiful spot to have your breakfast. Vibe with friends with mouth watering food alongside. Their Hummus platter is exotic and so is their jumjum rice. And craft beer is also available. All the Lebanese food I tried really blew my mind-away. It was so so so delicious. A hidden gem in Goa. Must visit spot.

I'm back to Mumbai, but I definitely miss Kefi and their breakfast. The atmosphere was charm and welcoming, and the preparation of eggs & coffee was just the way to start the day.

üç∞ It first got my attention when I saw they had Burnt Basque cake. Being Basque, I couldn't stop myself and had to try it. The cake was so yummy and smooth. It literally tasted like home.

‚òïÔ∏è coffees are a bliss. From the tiramisu coffee to the regular cold coffee, both options tasted intense and creamy at the same time.

üç≥ Lebanese eggs were the change-maker. I was afraid to try as there's a chilli on the menu stating that might be spicy but it was SO not spicy. Just the way I like it. I ordered twice in different days, and if I was still in Goa, I would have definitely started my day there.

üë•Ô∏è Staff were welcoming and professional.  They made sure you were comfortable without being intrusive. I recommend this place 100% to anyone visiting Goa. Even though you are not in a nearby area, try to make some time to visit if you are a foodie!

Goa has lot of new age cafe which serves global cuisine but this is my go out place for some high quality Mediterranean/middle estern food in goa. The vibe is pretty laid back at this place and some nice jazz really adds to that. I like the platter that they serve which is like a no brainer every-time i visit, and the coffee is also just perfect roast for my liking. We do give it a try to new dishes from their menu, sometimes it works out some times it doesn‚Äôt, like it didn‚Äôt work when I order ful mudammas. The pastry section has wide variety, tiramisu was decadent although bit pricey for the portion. On my suggestion, do give a try to muhammara which is rated as best dips in the world and kefi does it nicely.

description:
Nestled in the vibrant heart of Mapusa, Kefi - A Lebanese Caf√© and Bistro and Bar shines as a culinary gem, earning an impressive overall rating of 4.5 from an enthusiastic crowd of 1,300 patrons. This delightful establishment is known for its tantalizing Lebanese food, refreshing smoothies, Levantine specialties, and fragrant pilaf, making it a must-visit spot for anyone craving a taste of the Mediterranean in Goa.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Kefi, guests are greeted with a charming and welcoming atmosphere that exudes a relaxed yet sophisticated vibe. The d√©cor strikes a perfect balance between contemporary and traditional Lebanese elements, adorned with warm lighting that creates an inviting space for diners to mingle. The tasteful use of vibrant colors, coupled with decor pieces reflecting Levantine culture, enhances the culinary experience. The soft melodies of smooth jazz waft through the air, setting the stage for a leisurely dining experience, as reflected in the customer reviews.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Kefi's menu is a culinary journey into the heart of Lebanese and Middle Eastern cuisine. Signature dishes such as the exotic hummus platter and the flavorful jumjum rice have garnered rave reviews, with guests noting that every bite is a burst of deliciousness. The presentation of the food is equally impressive‚Äîdishes arrive beautifully arranged, elevating the dining experience to a feast for the eyes as well as the palate. Breakfast enthusiasts will be delighted by the famous Lebanese eggs and the coveted Burnt Basque cake, which has captivated taste buds with its creamy texture and rich flavor. Notably, vegetarian options abound, including the much-praised muhammara dip, regarded as one of the best globally.

### Customer Experience & Service

Guests consistently mention the friendly and professional staff at Kefi, who are dedicated to ensuring a comfortable dining experience. Attentiveness without being intrusive has been a hallmark of the service here, making diners feel valued. The caf√© accommodates both reservation and walk-in policies, allowing for flexibility whether you're planning a special brunch with friends or a spontaneous dining adventure. Customers have expressed their appreciation for the efforts made by the staff to deliver prompt service, ensuring food and drinks flow smoothly.

### Popularity & Reviews

Kefi has created quite a buzz on social media, with foodies sharing their unmatched experiences and mouthwatering photos of the dishes. Customer sentiment is overwhelmingly positive, as reflected in the reviews. Many consider it their go-to spot for quality Mediterranean cuisine amid Goa's bustling caf√© scene. The caf√© has garnered attention not only for its food but also for its inviting atmosphere, making it a top recommendation for both locals and visitors alike.

### Utilizing Visual Content

Supporting this narrative, customer-provided photos vividly capture Kefi's ambiance and culinary delights. Images showcase beautifully plated dishes, the inviting decor of the caf√©, and patrons enjoying their meals in a warm setting, highlighting the charm that draws people back time and time again. The colors and presentations depicted in these snapshots reflect the essence of Kefi's menu and the inviting atmosphere that wraps around every individual who steps inside.

### Conclusion

In conclusion, Kefi - A Lebanese Caf√© and Bistro and Bar stands out as a must-visit destination in Goa, where delectable Lebanese dishes meet an inviting ambiance and exemplary service. Whether indulging in smooth smoothies or exploring their extensive pilaf selection, visitors are sure to discover a culinary experience that captivates both their taste buds and hearts.
